    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Vice Consul at Hanoi (
                        O’Sullivan
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v08</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d54</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">54</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-05-21T01:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-05-21T01:00:00-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-05-21T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-05-21T01:00:00-05:00" n="54" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d54">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851G.00/5–2146: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Hanoi</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">O’Sullivan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanoi</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-05-21T13:00:00+07:00">May 21, 1946—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received May 22—1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Foreign Minister Nyugen Tuong Tarn today informed me he expected negotiations
                    would commence about June 15 and he thought they would last about 20 days.</p>
                <p>Tam indicated that Vietnamese delegation might be composed of as many as 30
                    persons. He said that personnel had not yet been decided upon but that it was
                    possible Ho Chi Minh might head mission.</p>
                <p>Sent <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>; repeated Nanking, Saigon informed
                    airmail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">O’Sullivan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
